		<L2>1. Go back</L2>
		<L2></L2>
		<L2>Camera controls:</L2>
		<L2>W/S - Move camera back and forth</L2>
		<L2>A/D - Move camera left and right</L2>
		<L2>Q/E - Move camera up and down</L2>
		<L2>Arrows Up/Down - Set orientation of the camera along its X axis (up and down)</L2>
		<L2>Arrows Left/Right - Set orientation of the camera along global Y axis (Left and Right)</L2>
		<L2>Key Minus (-) and Key Equal (=) - Set the zoom (FOV) level up and down</L2>
		<L2>F - Set wire-frame mode on/off</L2>
		<L2></L2>
		<L2>Balls controls:</L2>
		<L2>They are similar to the camera controls, except for the arrows</L2>
		<L2>B - cycles through the balls</L2>
		<L2>Once you select a ball with B you are in "Control Mode". To release the ball press "0"</L2>
		<L2>L - Lock-on mode. To release the ball, also press "0"</L2>
		<L2></L2>
		<L2>P - changes the current physics engine</L2>
	</Languange>

